# BX Finance UI Quality Rules

Before modifying any UI file in `banking_api_ui/src/`, run:

```bash
npm run test:e2e:score
```

This prints a 100-point score. Your changes must not lower it.

## Protected CSS classes — do not rename or remove

These classes are referenced by Playwright tests and have caused regressions when renamed.

### Token Chain Display
- `.tcd-root` — root container (whole component will disappear if removed)
- `.tcd-header-title` — must contain "Token Chain"
- `.tcd-tabs`, `.tcd-tab` — tabs "Current call" and "History"
- `.tcd-badge` — status badges (Active/Acquired/Exchanged/Failed)
- `.tcd-legend`, `.tcd-legend-item`
- `.token-info-btn` — dashboard button that opens the token modal

### Banking Agent
- `.banking-agent-fab` — floating action button (must show 🏦 icon)
- `.banking-agent-panel` — the panel itself
- `.ba-title` — must contain "BX Finance AI Agent"
- `.ba-left-col`, `.ba-right-col` — two-column layout
- `.ba-action-item` — action buttons (8 required: 🏦📋💰⬇⬆↔🔧🚪)
- `.ba-server-chip` — connected services chips
- `.banking-agent-messages` — chat message area
- `.ba-input`, `.ba-send-btn`

### Customer Dashboard
- `.user-dashboard` — root (used by all dashboard tests)
- `.accounts-grid`, `.account-card`, `.account-type-badge`, `.balance`
- `.transactions-table`, `.transaction-row`
- `.transaction-date`, `.transaction-type`, `.transaction-amount`, `.transaction-description`
- `.interface-indicator`, `.interface-icon`
- `.logout-btn` — must be visible and non-overlapping with FAB
- `.deposit-btn`, `.withdraw-btn`, `.select-account-btn`

### Landing Page
- `.brand-name` — must contain "BX Finance"
- `.feature-card` — 6 required
- `.step` — 3 required

## Data formatting rules (never regress these)

- **Currency**: always `$1,500.00` format — never raw `1500` or `1500.0`
- **Dates**: always human-readable — never ISO 8601 `2026-03-01T10:00:00.000Z`
- **Errors**: friendly messages only — never stack traces (`at Object.`) visible in UI
- **Toasts**: max 1 per page load — check `.Toastify__toast` count

## After finishing UI changes

```bash
npm run test:e2e:quality   # all 22 quality checks must pass
npm run test:e2e:score     # score must be ≥ 85 for a healthy UI
```

The full criteria are in `docs/ui-quality-criteria.md`.
